rnal Affairs, the Six Day War between Israel and Egypt, and the October Crisis in 1970.Starnes's memoir offers a fascinating look at Canada's security and intelligence work from the point of view of an official deeply involved in many covert government activities. It provides an insider's perspective on both the little-known world of the Canadian intelligence community and the international security and intelligence network in which Canada has participated. Written by the author of five spy novels, it will interest those who follow the history of Canada's undercover operations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aIntelligence officerszCanadavBiography. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Personal Memoirs.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144267302140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442673021423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781442673021/original  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles